<br>
The scenario:<br>
<br>
You have a spouse or partner who does not play EQ and is pretty computer illiterate.  They're happy you're keeping entertained, but not interested in touching the 'complicated machine'.  When they're busy/away, you enjoy your social life online.  In fact, you RP relationships for your characters, including detailed cyber.  <br>
<br>
Is it OK to RP relationships including cyber by your morals and ethics?<br>
<br>
A. Yes, it's perfectly fine.  So I don't need to try to explain RP and cyber to the spouse - even if I explained and s/he objected, it would still be fine to cyber, because it's not real.  <br>
<br>
B. Yes, as long as I tried to explain RP and cyber to the spouse and s/he said I could do it.<br>
<br>
C. No, I would never do this even if my spouse said it was OK.  It is cheating of a form and I think it's morally wrong.<br>
<br>
D. No, I would never do this even if my spouse said it was OK.  I don't consider it cheating, but it is morally wrong for other reasons.<br>
<br>
E. Other.<br>
